\begin{align*}
z w + 20i &= 5w + iw \\
wz + 12i &= -4z + 10iz
\end{align*}

Now, let's rearrange the equations to group the real and imaginary terms:

\begin{align*}
zw - iw &= 5w - 20i \\
wz - 10iz &= -4z - 12i
\end{align*}

We can now equate the real and imaginary parts of each equation:

\begin{align*}
zw &= 5w \\
-iw &= -20i \\
wz &= -4z \\
-10iz &= -12i
\end{align*}

